{
  "text": "When the production process is driven by an aggregated sales forecast, the firm can achieve high and stable capacity utilization and economies of scale by batching orders [CITATION_1] ). Raw-material producers, such as steel mills, often use forecasts to obtain the stable and sophisticated production schedules their equipment requires. On the downside, forecast-driven systems rely on costly inventories of finished goods, and forecast errors may cause them to hold obsolete inventory or to fail to fill customers' orders promptly.",
  "citation_candidates": [
